UML:TaggedValue.value: Unauthenticated users are allowed to view publicly accessible studies without logging in. These users will be able to use all of the study functionality described in the caIntegrator 2 use cases with the exception that they will not be able to save queries, lists, etc.

2. The Research Investigator selects the study he wishes to use from a list of subscribed studies.
3.The workspace displays the following items that may be opened in the workspace... (see UC for details)
4. The user selects one of the study items listed above, invoking the associated use case functionality.

A Research Investigator may subscribe himself to any publicly visible study. Similarly, a Research Investigator may request to be subscribed to restricted visibility studies, though these will not be accessible until the Study Author accepts the subscription request.
1. As a result of logging in, the Research Investigator is presented with his workspace set to display his default study (see Alternative Flow: Set Default Study).

If a Research Investigator is subscribed to multiple studies, he may choose to select any of these studies as the default that is opened at login. If the Research Investigator is only subscribed to a single study, it is automatically the default.
